  <brief_title>Trial for Treatment of Adult Patients With Standard Risk Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia With Chemotherapy and Rituximab</brief_title>
  <official_title>German Multicenter Trial for Treatment Optimisation in Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia in Adults and Adolescents Above 15 Years With Rituximab for Improvement of Prognosis in CD20 Positive Standard Risk ALL (Amend 2)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Johann Wolfgang Goethe University Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Johann Wolfgang Goethe University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study evaluates the efficacy and tolerability of an intensified induction and
      consolidation therapy in combination with rituximab in CD20 positive standard risk patients.
      Thereafter patients receive additional consolidation and reinduction cycles combined with
      rituximab. In parallel minimal residual disease is evaluated. After six months and one year
      the decision on intensification or discontinuation of therapy is made based on results of MRD
      evaluation
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
